elements.content: The cis-dichlorobis(diethyl succinate)titanium(IV) bis(hexachloroantimonate(V))−dichloromethane(1/1) salt, [cis-{C2H4(CO2Et)2}2Cl2Ti][SbCl6]2·CH2Cl2 (1), was prepared by direct reaction of TiCl4, diethyl succinate, and SbCl5 in CH2Cl2. catena-(μ-Diethyl succinate-O,O‘)bis(diethyl succinate-O,O‘)magnesium(II) tetrachloromagnesate(II)−dichloromethane(1/2), [Mg{C2H4(CO2Et)2}3][MgCl4]·2CH2Cl2 (2), was formed by substitution of ethyl acetate in [MgCl2(CH3CO2Et)] for diethyl succinate. Both species have been structurally characterized. Complex 1 crystallized in the space group Pnn2, with a = 16.178(5), b = 12.784(4), and c = 10.427(2) Å. Compound 2 belongs to the C2/c space group with a = 26.121(6), b = 10.086(2), c = 17.947(4) Å and β = 116.76(3)°. In the [cis-{C2H4(CO2Et)2}2Cl2Ti]2+ cation, the titanium atom is octahedrally coordinated by two mutually cis chlorine atoms and four carbonyl oxygen atoms of two chelating diethyl succinate molecules. The ([Mg{C2H4(CO2Et)2}3]2+)∞ cation in the crystalline state is a linear polymer formed by the [Mg{C2H4(CO2Et)2}2]2+ units linked by other diethyl succinate ligands. In this cation, each magnesium atom is octahedrally coordinated by six carbonyl oxygen atoms of ethyl succinate molecules. Catalytic activity was found for ethylene polymerization by 1.

Abstract published in Advance ACS Abstracts, February 15, 1996.

Introduction

The high reactivity and isospecifity in α-olefin polymerizations of group 4 metallocene/methylalumoxane homogeneous catalysts are attributed to the presence of cationic [M(Cp)2R]+ (M = Ti, Zr, Hf) species. Such cations could be simply formed by ion transfer, e.g. in the reaction between titanocene dichloride and methylaluminum dichloride. The alternative routes to [M(Cp)2R]+ are halide elimination using sodium tetraphenylborate, oxidation of a titanium(III) species by silver tetraphenylborate, and protolysis with elimination of methane of [Ti(Cp)2Me2] using [HNR3][BPh4] where R = CH3, Et, or n-Bu. The use of ethylaluminum ethoxide, dimethylaluminum methoxide, or diethylaluminum methoxide in the reaction with [VCl3(THF)3] leads to the [V2(μ-Cl)3(THF)6][AlR2Cl2] salt. Therefore it could be expected that also in the heterogeneous modern highly active polypropylene MgCl2/TiCl3/AlEt3 catalyst ionic species are present. The enhancement of isospecific activity of such catalysts is strongly dependent on an electron donor such as a carboxylic acid diester. It has been found that o-phthalate C6H4(CO2R)2 diesters yield with TiCl4 the monomeric [o-C6H4(CO2R)2Cl4Ti] compounds but with TiCl3 the dimeric [Ti2(μ-Cl)2Cl4{o-C6H4(CO2Et)2}2] complexes are formed. These compounds are good precatalysts for α-olefin polymerization processes. The product of direct reaction between a titanium diester compound and an organoaluminum compound is difficult to isolate in pure crystalline form. Alternatively, we have investigated the possibility of the formation of the [(diester)Cl3Ti]+ cation using SbCl5 as a chlorine-abstracting agent toward [(diester)Cl4Ti]. The chloride transfer between TiCl4 and SbCl5 in donor solvents, as a convenient synthetic route to discrete ionic titanium species is already well documented. The reactivity of MgCl2 toward a diester (both are catalyst components) and the influence of organic esters on MgCl2 ionization have been a matter of our interest as well. Here we describe a new simple high-yield method of synthesis leading to the [cis-{C2H4(CO2Et)2}2Cl2Ti][SbCl6]2·CH2Cl2 and [Mg{C2H4 (CO2Et)2}3][MgCl4]·2CH2Cl2 salts and report the details of their X-ray structures.

elements.content: Synthesis and Characterization of [ cis -{C2H4(CO2Et)2}2Cl2Ti][SbCl6]2·CH2Cl2 (1). The direct reaction of TiCl4 with diethyl succinate and SbCl5 in a 1:2:2 molar ratio in CH2Cl2 yields an air-sensitive, yellow compound of composition TiCl4·2SbCl5·2C2H4(CO2Et)2·CH2Cl2, which can be stored under N2. The new species 1 is diamagnetic. The IR spectrum shows stretching ν(CO) modes at 1555 (vs), 1565 (s), 1584 (vs), 1615 (s), and 1635 (s) cm-1 characteristic for coordinated ester molecules and bands at 400 (m), 431 (s), 463 (s), and 490 (m) cm-1 due to ν(Ti−Cl) and ν(Ti−O) vibrations. An intense sharp band at 342 cm-1 is characteristic for the [SbCl6]- anion; cf. K[SbCl6] with a ν(Sb−Cl) of 346 cm-1. The crystalline compound 1 is insoluble in hydrocarbons, and it is unstable in tetrahydrofuran, immediately undergoing decomposition, and as the result [TiCl4(THF)2] is formed. The composition of 1 and its IR spectrum suggested the compound to be a salt. This was confirmed by an X-ray structural study.

elements.content: X-ray Diffraction Study of 1. The results are presented in Table and Figure . Crystals of 1 consist of [cis-{C2H4(CO2Et)2}2Cl2Ti]2+ cations and [SbCl6]- anions in a 1:2 ratio. There is half of a nonassociated dichloromethane molecule in the asymmetric unit (the C(9) carbon atom from this molecule lies on the 2-fold axis). The solvent dichloromethane molecule in the unit cell results from crystallization. In the cation, the titanium atom is octahedrally coordinated by two mutually cis chlorine atoms and four carbonyl oxygen atoms from two diester molecules. The central atom lies on the 2-fold axis, which causes the cation as a whole to possess C 2 symmetry. Each diester molecule is coordinated to the Ti atom by two carbonyl oxygen atoms. The Ti−Cl(1) bond length of 2.175(8) Å is significantly shorter than those [average 2.252(2) Å] in [C2H4(CO2CH2CH2OPh)2Cl4Ti] and similar (within the range of standard deviations) to those found in [(CH3CN)3Cl3Ti]+ [average 2.186(5) Å]. The carbonyl group C(1)−O(1) remains in the preferred conformation, synperiplanar to the C(5)−O(3). Synthesis and Characterization of [Mg{C2H4(CO2Et)2}3][MgCl4]·2CH2Cl2 (2). The formation of [Mg(THF)6]2+, [MgCl(THF)5]+, [Mg2(μ-Cl)3(THF)6]+, and [MgCl4]2- ions from [MgCl2(THF)2] in tetrahydrofuran is well documented. The [MgCl2(CH3CO2Et)] compound in the presence of the diethyl succinate at a 2:3 ratio in dichloromethane gave a colorless air-sensitive compound formulated as 2MgCl2·3C2H4(CO2Et)2·2CH2Cl2 (2). Its IR spectrum presents the ν(Mg−Cl) stretching band at 370 (vs, br) cm-1, which is typical for the [MgCl4]2- anion, as well as a ν(CO) vibration at 1678 cm-1 characteristic for coordinated diethyl succinate molecules. The crystalline compound 2 has low solubility in halogenated solvents and is unstable in THF because the magnesium atom easily undergoes solvation and the complex [MgCl2(THF)2] is formed immediately. The presence of [MgCl4]2- in the IR and the composition of 2 suggested the species to be a salt.

elements.content: Polymerization Studies. The results of the ethylene polymerization test on [cis-{C2H4(CO2Et)2}2Cl2Ti][SbCl6]2·CH2Cl2 and six related compounds are shown in Table . The catalyst was prepared by milling an n-hexane slurry of MgCl2 and one of the compounds listed. Triethylaluminum was the cocatalyst. The highest activity [31 kg of PE/(g of Ti·h)] for [C2H4(CO2Et)2Cl4Ti] was reached at Mg:Ti = 10 and [Ti]0 = 0.05 mmol dm-3. In contrast, the catalytic activity for 1 at [Al] = 20 mmol was about 2 times lower [14.1 kg of PE/(g of Ti·h)] than that of [C2H4(CO2Et)2Cl4Ti]. Conclusions

These results cannot be explained simply, but some generalizations can be considered. The TiCl4 and MgCl2 compounds undergo ionization in the presence of diethyl succinate in dichloromethane to afford salts 1 and 2. In reaction 4, MgCl2 is simultaneously a Cl- donor and acceptor. In reaction 3, TiCl4 is a Cl- donor under treatment with a diester, which is used as internal and external donor for the preparation of the olefin polymerization catalyst, and gives the [{C2H4(CO2Et)2}2Cl2Ti]2+ cation. Hence ionization of MgCl2 and TiCl4 under the influence of a diester during the formation of an α-olefin polymerization catalyst could be also expected. elements.content: X-ray Data Collection and Refinement of the Structures (Table ). Data Collection and Processing. Preliminary data for both crystals were obtained from Weissenberg photographs. Intensities were collected using a Kuma KM4 four-circle diffractometer in the ω−2θ mode (with crystals of dimensions 0.5 × 0.3 × 0.3 mm for 1 and 0.6 × 0.5 × 0.4 mm for 2) and Mo Kα radiation. The crystals were cut from large crystals. Cell parameters were obtained from a least-squares fit of the setting angles of 25 reflections in the range 20° < 2θ < 27° for 1 and 2. The data collection was performed at T = 270.0(5) K for 1 and T = 180.0(5) K for 2 using an Oxford System Cryostream Cooler. The higher temperature of data collection for 1 was used because of a phase transformation occuring at approximately 180 K for crystals of 1. The measurement performed at a temperature closer to the temperature of phase transformation enhances thermal parameters of all atoms. The mentioned phase transformation presumably causes rearrangement of the [SbCl6]- anion. For both crystals, the intensities of three standard reflections, monitored every 100 intensity scans, showed no evidence of crystal decay. Totals of 3316 (4° < 2θ < 57°) and 8801 (4° < 2θ < 56°) reflections were measured for 1 and 2, respectively, from which 1137 and 2111 independent reflections with I > 3.0σ(I) were used for calculations. The structures were solved by the Patterson method and refined by full-matrix least-squares calculations using SHELXL93. The number of refined parameters was 199 for 1 and 219 for 2. Neutral-atom scattering factors and anomalous dispersion terms used in the refinement were taken from ref ; real and imaginary components of anomalous dispersion were included for all non-H atoms. The hydrogen atoms were placed in calculated positions with d(C−H) = 1.08 Å and introduced as fixed contributors in the final stage of refinement. The CH2Cl2 molecule in 1 lies on the 2-fold axis. Absorption corrections following the DIFABS procedure were applied for 2:  minimum and maximum absorption corrections were 0.876 and 1.038. Weighting schemes of the forms w = 1/σ2(F o 2) + (0.0383P)2 + 4.51P and w = 1/σ2(F o 2) + (0.0362P)2 + 27.97P (where P is defined as (F o 2 + 2F c 2)/3) were applied for 1 and 2, respectively. For the last cycle of the refinement, the maximum value of the ratio Δ/σ was below 0.005 Å for 1 and 2. The final difference map showed a general background within −0.30 and 0.47 for 1 and −0.42 and 0.48 e Å-3 for 2. Final R 1 and R 2w for the inverted structure of 1 are 0.0368 and 0.0874, respectively.
